channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Live Nation reveals ‘a criminal threat actor’ offered to sell Ticketmaster data on the dark web, while reports say hackers seek $500,000 for customer info
item.description: The data reportedly includes names, addresses, phone numbers and some credit card details of millions of Ticketmaster customers.

item.title: D.C. ethics board recommends Rudy Giuliani be disbarred
item.description: The recommendation comes after Giuliani represented Donald Trump in a Pennsylvania court case that sought to overturn the state’s 2020 election results.

item.title: First crewed launch of Boeing’s Starliner spacecraft scrubbed again
The housing market is finally seeing more inventory, but buyers aren’t showing up as a ‘cold reality is settling down’
item.description: “Without the rate cuts, a cold reality is settling down on the housing market,” Robert Frick, corporate economist for Navy Federal Credit Union, said.

item.title: Retired U.S. Navy admiral charged in bribery scheme with tech CEOs for $500,000 salary
item.description: Robert Burke started working as a senior partner at Next Jump with a starting annual salary of $500,000 and 100,000 stock options in 2022, the DOJ said.

item.title: Why the U.S. presidential election could aid summer stock market rally
The best-performing stock on the S&P 500 is a ‘unicorn’ that joined the index less than a month ago and is beating Nvidia
item.description: Vistra’s mix of gas and nuclear power plants make it “a unicorn,” according to Guggenheim’s Shahriar Pourreza.

item.title: Boeing, NASA cancel Starliner launch attempt scheduled Sunday after failed Saturday take-off
item.description: Boeing aimed to launch its first Starliner flight with astronauts on board on Saturday but called it off minutes before take-off.

item.title: Autodesk shares rally as internal audit eases accounting concern
The ANC party that freed South Africa from apartheid loses its 30-year majority, signaling first-ever coalition government to come
item.description: With more than 99% of votes counted, the once-dominant ANC had received just over 40% in Wednesday's election.

item.title: The SEC ruling on Ethereum ETFs could mark a historic shift in crypto investing
item.description: The VanEck CEO digs into the preliminary approval of his firm's Ethereum ETF and what the decision means for crypto investors.

item.title: Dow’s 575-point Friday surge puts finishing touch on year’s best month
Jerome Powell's Federal Reserve is stuck in a self-defeating paradox that makes cutting rates more difficult, economist warns
item.description: "You can call this the Fed Cut Reflexivity Paradox: The more the Fed insists that the next move in interest rates is a cut, the more financial conditions will ease, making it more difficult for the Fed to cut."

item.title: Honolulu is the western metro area where 1-bedroom rent has gone up the most in a year
item.description: CNBC Make It analyzed rent estimate data from Apartment List for April 2023 to April 2024, filtering metro areas by those with at least 500,000 residents.

item.title: Can a felon get a commercial real-estate loan?
